<HEADLINE> Santer Regards EU Executive Resignation as Political Act </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 16 (Xinhua) -- President Jacques Santer of the
European Commission said on Tuesday the commission's resignation
last night was a political act even though its members judge the
accusation from an independent report to be unbalanced.
</P>
<P>
The president, in a statement released here following the mass
resignation of all members of the executive body of the European
Union (EU), promised that "we would act on the report by the
committee of Independent Experts."
</P>
<P>
However, Santer alleged that the report's focus is on a small
number of specific cases which have recently attracted criticism
from the European Parliament.
</P>
<P>
"The cases are analyzed in great detail and, while the
findings reveal certain malfunctions and one instance of
favoritism, I would point out that there is no suggestion that any
member of the commission was involved in fraud or corruption or
stood to gain personally," said Santer.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the probe team only cited "a tiny number of cases
of fraud and malfunctioning", the President said the committee's
report paints a picture of total absence of responsibility on the
part of the EU executive branch and its officials.
</P>
<P>
"This picture is distorted. I consider the tone of the report's
conclusions to be wholly unjustified," he said.
</P>
<P>
The president also defended himself and all the president's men,
saying, "I do not accept that four years of work can be reduced to
six cases of irregularities, four of which date back to before
1995."
</P>
<P>
"I would also have hoped that the Committee of Independent
Experts might have attached appropriate significance to the very
substantial reforms carried out by this commission since 1995 and
the ambitious program announced to parliament last January," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The Committee of Independent Experts, set up on February 2,
said in its report that it found "instances where commissioners or
the commission as a whole bear responsibility" for the fraud,
irregularities or mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
Santer concluded that the commission as a caretaker executive
will continue to perform its functions until member states appoint
a new team under the Treaty of European Union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
