<HEADLINE> Dow Passes 10,000 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
passed 10,000 mark at 9:52 a.m. EST Tuesday but then gave a little
ground.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip stock index was down 16.09 at 9,942.68 about 20
minutes after breaking 10,000.
</P>
<P>
The index finished up 82.42 at 9,958.77, within 42 points of
10,000 Monday. The industrials were just 29.85 from the 10,000
milestone during the previous session of trading.
</P>
<P>
The index took almost a year to gain the final 1,000 points
after crossing 9,000 on April 6, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
