<HEADLINE> UK's Blair Says EC's Santer Must Go </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 16 (Xinhua) - British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said on Tuesday that European Commission President Jacques Santer
should step down as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
"The president of the Commission should leave as soon as
reasonably and practically possible and a new president should
take his place," Blair told parliament in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Blair said Santer was responsible for the resignation of the
Commission after an independent report accused it of corruption
and mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
"But I will be blunt. We cannot have the next president decided
in the same way as the last, debating the narrow interests of one
country or another.
</P>
<P>
"The top jobs, not just in the Commission, but throughout the
European institutions, should go to the top people. Merit and
merit alone should decide," Blair said.
</P>
<P>
Blair said next week's EU summit in Berlin should hammer out a
contract of reform for the Commission, including a complete
overhaul of financial control, a new system for monitoring
financial management and spending programs and new procedures
for awarding EU contracts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
