<HEADLINE> World Bank Expresses Support for Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank announced on
Tuesday its support for the Ecuadorean government's efforts to
bring the Latin American country out of its current economic
crisis.
</P>
<P>
"The current economic developments in Ecuador are a source of
great concern to us at the World Bank, as well as the entire
international community," World Bank President James D. Wolfensohn
said.
</P>
<P>
"The World Bank is ready to join in the development of a policy
framework for Ecuador, and to provide direct support for the
country to work its way out this crisis, while minimizing its
impact on the poor," he added.
</P>
<P>
World Bank officials are in Ecuador, along with officials from
the International Monetary Fund and the Inter-American Development
Bank, to assist the government in designing an emergency program
to help the country ride its way though this difficult situation,
the World Bank said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Ecuadorean President Jamil Mahuad announced last week a series
of austerity measures that have more than doubled fuel prices and
frozen many bank deposits in a bid to combat the country's worst
financial crisis in decades. 
</P>
</TEXT>
