<HEADLINE> NATO Hold Accession Ceremony for Three New Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) Tuesday hold an accession ceremony in its
headquarters here in Brussels for three new members from Eastern
European countries -- Czech Republic, Poland and Hungary.
</P>
<P>
NATO secretary General Javier Solana said at the ceremony that
the three countries have become full members of the Atlantic
Alliance.
</P>
<P>
Last week, The three new countries have formally accede to the
Washington Treaty which shaped the organization after World Two.
Now the NATO is a 19-member military power.
</P>
<P>
The NATO today received the prime ministers of the three new
members here in Brussels and the three nations' flags were raised
alongside those of the other 16 member countries at a ceremony of
welcome. Then the three ministers took their seats at the table of
the North Atlantic Council, NATO's decision-making body, as full
and equal NATO allies.
</P>
<P>
At its 50th anniversary celebrations in Washington later next
month, the NATO will proclaim a so-called "new strategy concept"
on orienting its future direction for the alliance of 19 members:
Belgium, Iceland, Denmark, Germany, France, Netherlands, Canada,
Luxemboug, the United States, Norway, Portugal, Turkey, Spain,
Greece, Italy, Britain, Poland, Hungary and Czech Republic.
</P>
