<HEADLINE> Serb Delegation Calls for Amending Agreement on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Serb President Milan
Milutinovic said on Tuesday that the political agreement on
autonomy in Kosovo should be amended and reaffirmed the rejection
by Belgrade of a deployment of NATO force in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The Serb delegation has submitted a proposal on amending the
political agreement on autonomy in Kosovo to the international
mediators and the representatives of the six-nation Contact Group.
</P>
<P>
This took place after the Kosovo Albanian delegation said on
Monday that it would sign the draft agreement on Kosovo prepared
by the international community.
</P>
<P>
``We are ready to sign political agreement. I say `political,'
but on condition that the amendments which we presented yesterday
should be accepted,'' said Milutinovic at the Center of
International Conference where the talks on Kosovo are being held.
</P>
<P>
He said that the amendments proposed by the Serbs fall in line
with the points of agreement reached in Rambouillet three weeks
ago.
</P>
<P>
``We are waiting for the answer to these proposals,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that the Yugoslav government has demanded that
there should be a political agreement first, and only after that
could the method on implementing the agreement be talked about.
</P>
<P>
``First a political agreement and afterwards only a discussion
on its implementation,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
On the sending of a NATO-led international force to Kosovo,
Milutinovic answered, ``It has been clearly rejected by our
people.'' 
</P>
