<HEADLINE> UN Approves Additional Five Contracts for Iraq's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council's Sanctions Committee approved additional five
contracts for Iraq's oil industry last week, the U.N. Office of
the Iraq Program (OIP) said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
OIP said the approved five contracts are worth 6,524,196, U.S.
dollars, bringing the total approved to 391 worth 236, 014,692
dollars.
</P>
<P>
