282, 642, 403 dollars and there are currently 94 contracts on hold
worth 28, 635, 264 dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the oil-for-food program, Iraq is allowed to
sell 5,2 billion worth of oil in every six months to purchase
necessities for its people who have been under sanctions since
1990. Under the current phase, Iraq can import 300 million dollars
worth of spare parts for its shabby oil industry.  
