warplanes patrolling the no-fly zones almost occurred every day
since the mid-December U.S.-British air strikes against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-led western allies imposed the no-fly zones in Iraq
in the wake of the 1991 Gulf War with a claimed aim of protecting
the Kurds in the north and the Shiite Muslims in the south from
what they call "Baghdad's suppression."
</P>
<P>
Iraq has declared that it does not recognize the no-fly zones
and will fire at any allied warplanes violating its airspace.
</P>
