<HEADLINE> Iran Releases 450 Iraqi POWs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Monday released some 450
Iraqi prisoners of war (POWs), said an Iraqi foreign ministry
spokesman on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi News Agency quoted the unnamed spokesman as saying
they are the first group of remaining Iraqi POWs to be freed
by Iran.
</P>
<P>
The move came under an agreement signed in the fourth meeting
of the Iraqi-Iranian joint committee for POWs held in Tehran on
November 14 to 26 last year.
</P>
<P>
These POWs should have been set free on December 23 last year
under the deal, said the spokesman, adding another group of POWs
should have been released on January 23, 1999.
</P>
<P>
However, some obstacles led to the delay of such release as
scheduled, said the spokesman without elaborating.
</P>
<P>
In return, the Iraqi government released 54 Iranian detainees
and prisoners to show Iraq's good will.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi foreign ministry appreciates the Iranian initiative
in releasing the Iraqi POWs and hopes that all the remaining Iraqi
POWs will be set free soon so as to end up their sufferings and
those of their families, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Iran, two former foes that fought an eight-year
bitter war in the 1980s, have improved relations since early last
year by swapping POWs and exchanging remains of those killed in
the 1980-1988 war. 
</P>
