<P>
"The law is very important and we are late for passing it as
all developed countries have approved it," Berri added.
</P>
<P>
The legislation of copyrights law came under the strong
pressure from western countries, especially the United States,
and international software companies.
</P>
<P>
Software manufacturers have complained that they lost millions
of dollars each year due to illegal software production in
Lebanon, where the piracy rate is estimated at 80 percent or
higher.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. software giant Microsoft Co. has said it will not open
a regional office in Beirut until Lebanon ratifies a bill on
intellectual property rights.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese parliament has been hesitating to pass the law
because some of its lawmakers fear an anti-piracy law will
eventually harm the interests of students who can not afford to
buy the costly original softwares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
