<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Army, Police Fights Kosovo Separatists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Yugoslavia, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav
troops and police fought with Kosovo separatists on Tuesday after
they were attacked by mortars and automatic weapons.
</P>
<P>
The troops and police, who were doing their field drills in
northern Kosovo, returned fire and forced the armed separatists
back into nearby Mount Cicavica, according to sources of the
Yugoslav Third Corps in Pristina.
</P>
<P>
The fights took place around the villages in between Kosovska
Mitrovica and Vucitrn, some 35 kilometers north of the capital of
the Yugoslav province.
</P>
<P>
The army brought in reinforcement of tanks and armored
personnel carriers and suffered no casualties during the ensuing
clash, the military sources said.
</P>
<P>
The clash was confirmed by the Kosovo Verification Mission of
the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe, that sent
several of its orange-colored jeeps and armored jeeps to the
fighting spots, where a couple of houses were hit by the
cross-fires.
</P>
<P>
Armed clashes kept breaking up in the past few days, even on
the day when the Kosovo peace talks resumed Monday in Paris.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav army and police had fended off the offensives from
the separatists in Kosovo. 
</P>
