<HEADLINE> Riyadh Urges Further Efforts to Combat Drug Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia Tuesday voiced
its utmost concern over the worsening drug problem and called on
the world community to combat drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
In a speech to the 42nd international conference on drugs held
at the U.N. headquarters in Vienna, Saudi Interior Assistant
Undersecretary Saleh Al-Sheikh said his country is greatly
concerned about the expansion of the illegal plantation of
narcotics in some countries.
</P>
<P>
