dopes from drugs and called for further international control on
drug abuse, Saleh was quoted as saying by the Saudi Press Agency
monitored here.
</P>
<P>
Riyadh favors boosting world cooperation in combating drug
abuse and money laundering to tighten the noose on drug
traffickers, the Saudi official said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the Gulf kingdom's intention to continue to crack
down on drug trafficking by applying tough penalties.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, Saudi Arabia, like other oil-rich Gulf
countries, is becoming one of the major targets of drug
traffickers.
</P>
<P>
The kingdom, which adopts a strict policy against narcotics,
imposes capital punishment on drug smugglers and dealers. 
