<HEADLINE> Factfiles of Expelled IOC Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Following are profiles of the
six members expelled by the International Olympic Committee on
Wednesday for their role in Salt Lake bribery scandal:
</P>
<P>
Lamine Keita (Mali)
</P>
<P>
Born: August 8, 1944 in Bamako.
</P>
<P>
Education: Engineer.
</P>
<P>
Olympic career: President of Malian National Olympic Committee,
vice-president of International Basketball Federation, vice-
president of the Islamic Fderation of Olympic Solidarity.
</P>
<P>
Member of the IOC since 1977.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Claude Ganga (Congo)
</P>
<P>
Born: 28 February, 1934.
</P>
<P>
Education: French youth and sports inspectorate diploma.
</P>
<P>
Olympic career: Founder member of Congolese Olympic Committee
and several national sports federations (from 1960). President of
Congolese NOC (from 1989), president of the Association of
National Olympic Committees of Africa (from 1989).
</P>
<P>
Member of the IOC since 1986.
</P>
<P>
Sergio Santander (Chile)
</P>
<P>
Born: May 22, 1926 in Peumo.
</P>
<P>
Education: Chartered Accountant.
</P>
<P>
Olympic career: President of Chilean Olympic Committee (from
1988). Member of IOC Sport for All Commission (from 1992)
</P>
<P>
Member of the IOC since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Agustin Carlos Arroyo (Ecuador)
</P>
<P>
Born: July 22, 1923 in Guayaquil.
</P>
<P>
Education: Degree in philosophy and social sciences, Doctor of
Civil and Canon Law, member of the Bar of Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
Sport: Recipient of national and regional awards in the
following sports -- boxing, table tennis, swimming, riding,
wrestling, weightlifting, judo and shooting.
</P>
<P>
Olympic career: President of Ecuadorean Olympic Committee (1964-
1968), Member of IOC juridical commission (1983-1987 1993-present),
member of Court of Arbitration for Sport (1983).
</P>
<P>
Member of the IOC since 1968.
</P>
<P>
Zein El Abdin Abdel Gadir (Sudan)
</P>
<P>
Born: May 7, 1940 in Khartoum.
</P>
<P>
Education: Sudan Military Academy.
</P>
<P>
Sport: National military soccer team.
</P>
<P>
Career: Founder of the first Sudanese Parachute regiment, 1963,
Minister for Youth, Sport and Social Affairs, 1974-80.
</P>
<P>
Olympic Career: President of the Sudanese Olympic Committee (
1980-87). IOC member from 1983 to 1987 and from 1990.
</P>
<P>
Seiuli Paul Wallwork (Samoa)
</P>
<P>
Born: January 15, 1942.
</P>
<P>
Occupation: Permanent secretary Ministry of Youth, Sports and
Cultural Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Olympic career: Chef de Mission for South Pacific Games,
Commonwealth Games, executive director of the seventh South
Pacific Games, chairman of Samoan Olympic Committee, chairman of
national boxing federation (1984-87), vice-chairman Samoa Rugby
Football Union (1982-86).
</P>
<P>
IOC member since 1987.
</P>
</TEXT>
