<HEADLINE> Police Seize One Ton of Narcotics in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Tehran police seized more than one
ton of narcotics and arrested 8,000 people for drug offenses
during the current Iranian calendar year to end on March 20, a
senior police officer said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Nasser Aslani, head of the anti-drug police in Tehran
province, said his forces confiscated 1,380 kilograms of drugs and
arrested more than 1,000 dealers and 6,748 addicts during the year.
</P>
<P>
Some 170 tonnes of various narcotics have been seized
throughout the country during the past 11 months of the year,
according to officials of the Iranian anti-drug headquarters
recently.
</P>
<P>
Iran has been committed to crackdown on drug smuggling since
1989 after its parliament passed a strict law, under which any one
caught with more than 30 grams of heroin or five kilograms of
opium will be sentenced to death.
</P>
<P>
Reports said more than 3,000 drug dealers have been executed
since the law took effect, but there are no official figures to
confirm the reports. 
</P>
