<HEADLINE> Kosovo Conference to End in Hours: EU Mediator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) mediator at
the conference on Kosovo, Wolfgang Petritsch, said Tuesday
afternoon that the conclusion of the conference on Kosovo was "no
more than a matter of hours".
</P>
<P>
"This is only a question of hours. Beyond that, we will no
more available for the negotiations and the talks on the agreement,
" Agence France-Presse (AFP) quoted the Austrian diplomat as
saying.
</P>
<P>
AFP said that international mediators and the six-nation
Contact Group are losing hope in persuading the Serbs to accept
the peace plan.
</P>
<P>
The Serbs said on Tuesday that not only do they reject a
deployment of NATO force in Kosovo, the political part of the
peace plan should also be amended in some aspects.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo Albanian delegation said they would accept the plan
on establishing autonomy in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The three international mediators -- U.S. diplomat Christopher
Hill, Russian diplomat Boris Mayorski and Petritsch -- will give a
press conference in the late afternoon Wednesday. 
</P>
