<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Solve Cultural Relics Theft Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 17 (Xinhua)-- Chinese police have recovered
stone horses, Buddha, tablets, and other cultural relics and have
arrested two suspects in a major theft case.
</P>
<P>
On the evening of March 10, police in the city of Zhengzhou in
central China's Henan Province became suspicious of two men
covering up some goods in a truck and discovered some objects
among them that were likely to be relics stolen from a Buddhist
temple.
</P>
<P>
They later confirmed that the 11 objects, which weighed more
than 10 tons, were all relics that dated back to the Ming and Qing
dynasties (1368-1911) and were on the country's protection list.
</P>
</TEXT>
