<HEADLINE> China Opens Environmental Protection Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua)-- China wants to get the average
Chinese citizen involved in environmental protection, which has
been mainly been a government activity in the past.
</P>
<P>
The ministries of education, construction, railways, water
resources, forestry, and six government departments discussed the
details of the massive campaign today via a telephone conference.
</P>
<P>
They decided that, for the March-June period, the campaign will
mainly take the form of planting trees and getting rid of plastic
garbage, or "white garbage", in tourist spots, rivers, lakes, and
along railway lines.
</P>
<P>
The second part of the campaign, from July to October, will
tackle air pollution, heavy car exhaust, dust pollution at
construction sites, waste gas and water emissions of factories,
and roadside food businesses in particular.
</P>
<P>
Liu Qibao, the deputy secretary-general of the State Council,
says that the purpose of the clean-up campaign is to create a
clean and beautiful environment to welcome the 50th anniversary of
New China. They need to try to increase people's awareness of the
need for environmental protection and sustainable development, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
