<HEADLINE> Profile of IOC President Samaranch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUSANNE, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Following are facts about Juan
Antonio Samaranch, president of the International Olympic
Committee (IOC):
</P>
<P>
Born: July 17, 1920 in Barcelona
</P>
<P>
Education: Higher Institute of Business Studies, Barcelona.
Higher diploma in Business Studies.
</P>
<P>
Languages: Spanish, French and English.
</P>
<P>
Career: Economics professor, member of the board of several
banks, Municipal Councilor responsible for sport in Barcelona,
Spanish Ambassador to the former Soviet Union and Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Sports: Hockey, boxing, soccer.
</P>
<P>
Sports administration: President of Spanish Olympic Committee.
Chef de Mission at Olympic Games (Cortina d'Ampezzo 1956, Rome
1960, Tokyo 1964)
</P>
<P>
IOC career: Member since 1966. Member of Executive Board (1970-
1978 and 1979 to present), vice-president (1974-1978), president (
1980 to present). 
</P>
</TEXT>
