<HEADLINE> Chinese State Council Discussing New Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The executive committee of the
Chinese State Council met today in Beijing and approved in
principle three new drafts of laws.
</P>
<P>
The drafts are for a bid invitation law, a public housing fund
management regulation, and an entertainment site management
regulation.
</P>
<P>
The committee members said that a law on handling bids is
significant as a guarantee of quality at construction sites and a
way to halt corrupt practices in those projects.
</P>
<P>
The members agreed that it would be submitted to the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress for approval after
further amendments are made and that the two regulations would
also be subject to further amendments before being accepted by the
State Council.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was presided by Premier Zhu Rongji.  
</P>
</TEXT>
