<HEADLINE> Soeharto's Son-in-law Summoned by Armed Forces Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Armed Forces (ABRI)
Commander Gen. Wiranto has summoned Lt. Gen. (ret.) Prabowo
Subianto for a clarification of the meeting of May 14, 1998, ABRI
spokesman Maj. Gen. Syamsul Maarif told reporters here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Prabowo, son-in-law of former president Soeharto, was dismissed
from ABRI last year after a special military council found that
soldiers under his command in the Special Forces (Kopassus) had
kidnapped anti-Soeharto activists.
</P>
<P>
Once the fastest rising general in the military, Prabowo's star
tumbled after Soeharto quit on May 21 last year. He was sacked
from his position as chief of the Army's Strategic Reserves
(Kostrad) and transferred to a training college.
</P>
<P>
There was an indication that the May 14 meeting was associated
with the May 13-15 riots in Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
A joint fact-finding team was established by the government to
investigate the riots in which 1,200 were killed, many of them
trapped in burning malls. The team has urged the government to
conduct further investigations into the riots, including the May
14 meeting.
</P>
<P>
The government has acknowledged that dozens of women were also
sexually assaulted, but it denied the team's conclusion that the
riots were organized.
</P>
<P>
According to Hashim Djojohadikusuma, Prabowo's younger brother,
Prabowo will soon return to Jakarta from Jordan.
</P>
<P>
"My brother Prabowo Subianto will arrive in Jakarta in April to
accept an invitation from General Wiranto, who has followed the
team's recommendation that Prabowo's presence at the meeting at
the Kostrad headquarters be clarified," Hashim said here Tuesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
