<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Tuesday destroyed seven Tamil rebel bunkers in Northern Province
of the country, a military spokesman said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ink Dewage said the troops observed a rebel stronghold and
destroyed seven rebel bunkers with the help of heavy machine guns
and rocket propelled grenades.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fired mortars and machine guns at the troops who
retaliated with artillery and mortar fire.
</P>
<P>
The troops confirmed that the rebels of the Liberation Tigers
of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) suffered heavy casualties due to the
artillery fire, Dewage said.
</P>
<P>
Four soldiers were also injured during the fighting, he said.
</P>
<P>
Also on Tuesday, government troops conducted a limited
operation in the east and west of Paranthan in a bid to destroy
rebel strongholds in the areas simultaneously, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The troops destroyed a rebel bunker line. The rebels fired at
the advancing troops with small arms and then fled, while the
troops killed at least four of the fleeing rebels with artillery
and mortar fire.
</P>
<P>
Government troops also reportedly killed at least eight rebels
in two separate incidents in the same area on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been waging a war against the government since
1983 for a separate state of its own in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
