<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique's multi-party
elections, the second of its kind, is to be held on October 27-28,
with the registration planned from June 1 to August 15, Alfredo
Gamito, the Minister of State Administration, announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Gamito said that about 1930 registration teams are to be set
up for the year's elections, 200 more than that in the first
general elections in October 1994, the Noticias daily reported
here Wednesday .
</P>
<P>
He said that the money for the elections, which is about 40.8
million U. S. dollars, is ready, adding that nearly 21 percent of
the money, about nine million dollars will come from the
Mozambican government, with the rest coming from the European
Union (23 million) and the United Nations Development Program (8
million).
</P>
<P>
The minister said the government had completed all the work for
the election in early February, like the re-organization of the
secretariat of technical and administrative committee for the
election and the preparation of materials for its operation.
</P>
<P>
He urged the parliament and other parties to speed up the
process of the establishment of the National Election Committee,
one of the key issues for the elections.
</P>
<P>
A resolution passed by the Mozambican parliament stipulates
that the number of the election committee members should be
enlarged from nine to 17,

among which eight are to come from the ruling Mozambican
Liberation Front, six from the National Resistance Movement of
Mozambique, the biggest opposition party, and one from the
Democratic Union. 
