<HEADLINE> Cambodian PM Returns From Indonesia Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister Hun
Sen returned home Wednesday from a three-day official visit to
Indonesia at the invitation of Indonesian President B.J. Habibie.
</P>
<P>
The entourage of the prime minister includes Minister of the
Council of Ministers Sok An and other officials.
</P>
<P>
Sok An said at the Pochentong international airport that Hun
Sen's was very successful, adding that Cambodia would officially
entry into the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) on
April 19 or 20.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Hun Sen met with President Habibie, and the
two leaders reached an agreement to strengthen bilateral relations
and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia pledged to continue to provide technical assistance
for Cambodia in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen and Habibie also discussed Cambodia's membership in
ASEAN. Hun Sen expressed his appreciation for Indonesia's support
for Cambodia's entry into ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the official ceremony to admit Cambodia
will be held during an ASEAN foreign ministers' meeting in Hanoi
on April 19. Cambodia was accepted as the 10th member of ASEAN
last December.
</P>
<P>
It was Hun Sen's second official visit to Indonesia. His first
visit was in 1994 when he was Cambodia's second prime minister.
