<HEADLINE> Foreign Ships Turn Into Money-Makers' Target in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Unlike the gunmen in southern Somalia who are busy in fighting
for clan motivations or extorting money from the commercial
traffic at roadblocks, the gunmen in northeastern somalia
construct heavy machine guns on speed boats with the aim of
improving their capacity in hunting for foreign fishing vessels.
</P>
<P>
The latest of such activities indicate that a Taiwanese fishing
boat was caught by Somali gunmen at Dhananeh beach of Eyl
district in the northeastern region of Nugal Monday afternoon .
</P>
<P>
According to the reports reaching here in Mogadishu, the
vessel was attacked by four speed boats with more than 30 heavily
armed men on board.
</P>
<P>
The reports did not say whether the Taiwanese vessel was
itself armed. But the VHF radio reports from the town of Eyl said
one of the speed boats which attacked the vessel together with
six of its staff members are still missing despite the victory of
conquering the fishing vessel.
</P>
<P>
Unlike other times, the gunmen who had captured the vessel
have refused access of anybody to see the foreigners on board the
vessel and their status.
</P>
<P>
However, some inner sources said the vessel is carrying 31
foreigners on board including Ugandans, Tanzanians, Indians and
other nationals. The gunmen holding the vessel and its crew
members said the foreign vessel was caught red-handed in fishing
illegally in the sea waters of northeastern Somalia.
</P>
<P>
The vessel is not the only one caught in recent days. Three
days ago, another foreign fishing vessel belonging to Ukraine was
similarly caught in Gabba coast of Eyl district in Mudug region.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the vessel having 19 crew members on
board, 18 Ukrainians and a Somali national, was caught while
allegedly conducting illegal fishing activities in Somalia's
economic exclusive sea waters in the Indian Ocean.
</P>
<P>
On February 18, an Italian ship with its 33 crew members were
released with a ransom of 230,000 U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
