<HEADLINE> 2 Policemen, Four Guards killed by Mine in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Two policemen and four home
guards were killed when Tamil rebels set off a claymore mine in
northern Sri Lanka on Wednesday, informed sources here said.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place at Manaduwa in Vavuniya in Northern
Province, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
A combined police and a home guard units were on a clearing
patrol in a tractor early in the morning when the mine went off,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Four others were injured in the explosion. Government troops
were combing the area to strengthen security in the region, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war against the
government for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country since 1983. 
