<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Italian Journalist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
with Ferruccio De Bortoli, director of Italy's Corriere Della Sera
newspaper, here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told his guest that he will soon pay a state visit to
Italy. "High-level reciprocal visits between our two countries
have become more frequent in recent years, giving impetus to our
cooperation in all fields," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that Italy as the birthplace of the Renaissance has had
many influential figures throughout history. "Both our nations
have a long civilization, and China and Italy share many
similarities, even though we are geographically far apart," he
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He said he considers bilateral cooperation in all fields to be
"conductive to enhancing mutual understanding," adding that the
press can play a significant part in this regard.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes Corriere Della Sera will comprehensively and
objectively cover events in China, and present more opportunities
for its readers to acquire a greater understanding of China's
history and reality.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also answered the paper's written questions on China's
domestic situation, Sino-Italian and Sino-European relations, and
the current international situation.
</P>
<P>
Bortoli expressed thanks for his meeting with Jiang prior to
the latter's upcoming European trip to Italy, Switzerland and
Austria.
</P>
<P>
Bartoli said the Italian people are looking forward to Jiang's
visit and hoped his interview will play a part in the growth of
the Italian-Chinese and European-Chinese relationships. 
</P>
