<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index dipped
0.05 of a point to 511.85, the all-share Emas index slipped 0.4 of
a point to 128.11, the Industrial index lost 0.93 of a point to
955.72 and the Second Board index eased 2.6 points to 122.21.
</P>
<P>
Losers led gainers by 454 to 115, while 161 counters were
unchanged, 179 untraded, and 23 others suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover was slightly better at 73.845 million
shares valued at 148.708 million ringgit (39.133 million U.S.
dollars) from Tuesday's 71.839 million shares worth 163.808
million ringgit (43.107 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
