<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Austrian Journalist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
with Kurt Seinitz, foreign editor of the Neue Kronen Zeitung
newspaper of Austria, here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told his guest that he will soon pay his first visit to
Austria at the invitation of his Austrian counterpart, Thomas
Klestil.
</P>
<P>
"Austria is the country of music with such great musicians as
Mozart and Strauss," he said, adding that musical exchanges have
constituted an important part of the cultural exchanges between
China and Austria and play its role in promoting mutual
understanding and friendship between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said that China attaches importance to
the growth of ties with Austria, and is delighted to see the ever
greater development of this relationship in all fields.
</P>
<P>
The press can play its part in the process, he said, adding
that China welcomes objective coverage of China. He also asked
Seinitz to convey his greetings to the Austrian people through his
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also answered the paper's written questions on China's
domestic situation, and Sino-Austrian and Sino-European relations.
</P>
<P>
Seinitz expressed thanks for his meeting with Jiang prior to
the latter's upcoming Austrian visit. He also conveyed greetings
from President Klestil to Jiang and wished Jiang's visit complete
success.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Seinitz recalled his China visit in 1972
and his meeting at that time with Premier Zhou Enlai. He told
Jiang he anticipates seeing the further growth of Austrian-Chinese
relations in the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
