<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan Drafts Regulations to Protect Ecology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The assessment, the first of its kind in China, was launched as
part of preparations to formulate a program to protect eco-tourism
resources in nature reserves, according to Gui Xiaojie, an
official with the Hunan Provincial Forestry Protection Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The plan, which will be drawn up in line with international
standards, will be unveiled at the end of April, said Gui.
</P>
<P>
Hunan's 33 nature reserves, which cover 540,000 hectares, are
home to more than 60 rare plant species, 76 rare animal species
and vast stretches of natural forests.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the protection program is to prevent ecological
deterioration related to the development of tourism resources.
</P>
</TEXT>
