<HEADLINE> Tajikistan Welcomes Progress in Afghan Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA-ATA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Tajikistan said Tuesday the
agreement reached in the Afghan peace talks would help set up a
normal political system in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Foreign Ministry said that Tajikistan
always stands for a peaceful and fair resolution of the Afghan
issue, supporting and promoting the peace talks. It called on the
warring factions to continue their dialog for the eventual
realization of peace in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman Vladimir
Rakhmanin Tuesday welcomed the progress made in the peace talks in
Ashgabat, Turkman capital, regarding it as a signal that the
warring factions are now willing to end the conflict and sit down
at the negotiation table.
</P>
<P>
He said the future of Afghanistan will be decided by whether
the warring factions will really implement their agreement,
realize a permanent cease-fire and form a coalition government
consisting of all factions.
</P>
<P>
On March 11, the Afghan warring parties began the second round
of peace talks in Ashgabat under the mediation of U.N.
representatives.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed on March 14 to form a coalition government,
exchange prisoners of war and continue their talks to end the
bloody conflict. 
</P>
</TEXT>
