<HEADLINE> Polish President Arrives for Visit to Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski arrived here Wednesday for a four-day official visit
to Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
An official welcoming ceremony was held by his Vietnamese
counterpart Tran Duc Luong at the Presidential Palace before the
two heads of state went into their official talks.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski, the first Polish Head of State to visit Vietnam in
40 years, is scheduled to meet with Vietnam's communist party
leader Le Kha Phieu and National Assembly Chairman Nong Duc Manh
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski's current Vietnam visit was described by leading
newspapers here as "an important event, opening up a new chapter
of development in bilateral friendship and cooperation between the
two countries."
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and Poland established diplomatic relations in 1950.
Since 1989, the relationship between the two countries has been
developing on "a new basis of equality and mutual benefit,"
official media here said.
</P>
<P>
Poland is the first East European country to write off over 80
percent of Vietnam's debts to Poland.
</P>
<P>
Last year Poland pledged a 70 million U.S. dollar loan to
Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
