<HEADLINE> "China's Tibet" Marks 10th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing hosted a forum today to
mark the 10th anniversary of the publication of "China's Tibet".
</P>
<P>
Representatives from ethnic minority, religious, Tibet studies,
press and publications communities in the Chinese capital attended
the forum.
</P>
<P>
Li Dezhu, deputy head of the United Front Work Department of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and minister
in charge of the State Ethnic Affairs Commission, reviewed the
magazine's contributions in publicizing Tibet, and noted that the
publication has been a major channel enabling readers from both at
home and abroad to learn more about the region.
</P>
<P>
Raidi, chairman of the Tibet Autonomous Region People's
Congress Standing Committee, said propaganda released by the Dalai
clique and anti-China forces has distorted living conditions and
social progress in the region.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted that the magazine has presented the world
with a true picture of Tibet.
</P>
<P>
"China's Tibet", the only Chinese publication focusing on Tibet,
is published bi-monthly in the Chinese, Tibetan and English
languages. The publication is currently distributed in 110
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The magazine has carried 1,980 wide-ranging articles covering
the protection of traditional Tibetan culture, as well as
archeology, natural resources and ecology in the region, over the
past decade.
</P>
<P>
"China's Tibet" has established an Internet website -- wws.
ctibet.org.cn -- offering readers online versions of the magazine
in both Chinese and English. Interested parties can use the
following E-mail address -- zgxzxs.@ctibet.org -- to contact the
magazine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
