<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Ministries Stress Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua)-- China launched a nationwide
campaign today with priority on afforestation and environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
Eleven departments, including the Cultural Ethics Office under
the Communist Party of China Central Committee, the ministries of
Education, Construction, Railway and Environmental Protection,
participated to today's teleconference announcing this year's plan
for afforestation, eliminating so-called "white" pollution,
improving air quality and controlling water contamination.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for strengthening urban afforestation and
protection of green areas during the prime growing season between
March and June.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should also focus on eliminating white pollution in
public areas, at scenic sites and along rivers and railways.
</P>
<P>
Plans for the period between July and October call for major
cities to focus greater efforts on controlling automobile
emissions, dust pollution at construction sites and industrial
pollution in order to improve urban air quality.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises discharging wastewater into rivers and lakes will
be punished according to laws and regulations.
</P>
<P>
Liu Qibao, deputy secretary-general of the State Council,
stressed that publics awareness of environmental protection must
be improved to ensure the success of the campaign.  
</P>
</TEXT>
