<HEADLINE> Hostage Taker Captured After Killing 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A hostage taker captured after
killing three people and wounding a housewife early Wednesday
morning was subjected to medical examination prior to the filing
of criminal charges against him.
</P>
<P>
Alfonso Bayot, just on his third day in Manila, slew the
victims with a bolo and a lead pipe and held three children
hostage.
</P>
<P>
The bloody hostage-taking incident took place at a two-storeyed
house. Three people, including a woman, were slain by the man.
</P>
<P>
A housewife sustained severe injuries and was in critical
condition at the hospital.
</P>
<P>
The suspect, investigators said, arrived in Manila with one of
the victims from Davao del Sur to work as houseboys under the
auspices of an employment agency.
</P>
<P>
But the two sneaked and went to the house of Eduardo Manggay,
another victim.
</P>
<P>
Investigators gathered that the suspect ran berserk when
Eduardo scolded him and told him to leave the house.
</P>
<P>
The suspect also turned on his companion when the latter tried
to stopped him.
</P>
<P>
Three children inside the house at the time were not harmed.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested the suspect and negotiations are under way.
</P>
