<HEADLINE> South Korea Urges U.S. to Normalize Ties with DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 17 (Xinhua) -- South Korea Wednesday urged the
United States to normalize relations with the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) to help facilitate Seoul's comprehensive
engagement policy toward the DPRK.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that normalization of relations between the United
States and North Korea will take place because it means a wider
opening up of North Korea to the world community," said South
Korean Minister for Foreign Affairs and Trade Hong Soon-young at
the Seoul Foreign Correspondents' Club.
</P>
<P>
He said the establishment of full diplomatic relationship
between the United States and the DPRK will help improve inter-
Korean relations and foster an atmosphere for peaceful co-
existence in the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister said official ties between Washington and
Pyongyang will be in line with the comprehensive engagement
strategy put forward by South Korean President Kim Dae-jung.
</P>
<P>
The minister's statement came soon after the DPRK and the
United States reached an agreement in New York Tuesday over
suspected underground nuclear site in DPRK's Kumchang-ni.
</P>
<P>
In the agreement, the DPRK promises to allow the United States
access to the suspected nuclear site while the latter pledges to
improve bilateral political and economic relations. 
</P>
