<HEADLINE> ARATS Delegation Arrives in Taipei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIPEI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Li Yafei, a deputy secretary
general of the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits
(ARATS), and his party arrived in Taipei this afternoon to
exchange views with the Straits Exchanges Foundation (SEF) on
ARATS President Wang Daohan's Taiwan visit.
</P>
<P>
Li said ARATS invited and received SEF Chairman Koo Chen-fu and
his party in the mainland last October, and noted that this visit
has improved cross-Straits relations and opened a new phase for
cross-Straits contacts and dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Wang and Koo met in Shanghai and reached a four-point consensus
under which ARATS and SEF will conduct talks on politics and
economy, exchange high-level visits, and increase mutual
assistance in cases involving the life and property of compatriots
on both sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, it was also agreed that Wang Daohan will
visit Taiwan at the proper time.
</P>
<P>
Li said that ARATS actively supports the implementation of the
consensus, and his Taiwan tour is being conducted precisely for
this purpose.
</P>
<P>
ARATS believes that Wang's Taiwan visit will be a significant
event in cross-Straits relations this year, Li said, and it is
willing to fully listen to SEF's opinions for making comprehensive
preparations for the visit.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that the Wang-Koo meeting has created a positive
atmosphere for cross-Straits relations, which must be cherished by
both sides.
</P>
<P>
He voiced the hope that ARATS and SEF will handle the four-
point consensus rationally, practically and soberly in order to
make certain that Wang's Taiwan visit further promote the
development of cross-Straits relations and meet the desires and
demands of compatriots on both sides.
</P>
<P>
Jan Jyh-horng, deputy secretary general of SEF, will host a
banquet this evening to welcome the four-member ARATS delegation.
</P>
