<HEADLINE> New Measures Protect Overseas Chinese Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The State Council announced new
measures today to further protect legitimate rights and interests
of overseas Chinese business people and investors from Hong Kong
and Macao.
</P>
<P>
An official with the State Council's Office of Overseas Chinese
Affairs said this year has been listed a "year for providing
expanded services for ventures funded by overseas Chinese."
</P>
<P>
