Chinese investors and business people from Hong Kong and Macao
during the Asian financial crisis will be one of the major duties
of overseas Chinese affairs departments.
</P>
<P>
Local governments and judicial departments will render
appropriate punishment to parties responsible for infringing on
the rights and interests of overseas Chinese investors.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that investments from overseas Chinese and
business people from Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan have accounted
for over 70 percent of direct overseas investment in China over
the past 20 years.  
