<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Obese Boy in China Loses 60 Kilograms in Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Deng Xuejian, believed to be the
heaviest 11-year-old boy in the world with a weight of 174
kilograms, has lost 60 kilograms since he began receiving medical
treatment at the Aimin weight-loss center in northern China's
Tianjin Municipality last September.
</P>
<P>
Deng's weight has been reduced from 174.25 to 114 kilograms in
the past six months, and his chest measurements have gone from 165
to 125 centimeters and waist from 154 to 113 centimeters.
</P>
<P>
"This is a very rare case," said one doctor. Five doctors at
the center worked out a special treatment plan for Deng focusing
on controlling his sleep, diet, and exercise, and they are
employing acupuncture and traditional Chinese medicine as well.
All his medical treatment is being provided free of charge.
</P>
<P>
According to the course of therapy, he is taking traditional
Chinese medicine and acupuncture every other day, running over 3,
000 meters and walking 20,000 meters everyday, and has an egg and
milk for breakfast and some meat and vegetables. Deng also has 100
grams of staple food for lunch, and vegetable and vitamins for
dinner.
</P>
<P>
The doctors want to see Deng lose an additional 50 kilograms
within the next six months, so he will then be able to live a
normal life among children of his own age.
</P>
<P>
Deng was born into a farm family in Tianjin's Baodi County and
weighed only three kilograms at birth. His weight increased to 15.
5 kilograms seven months later, and his weight continued to
increase by 10 to 15 kilograms every year since then.
</P>
<P>
His parents used to take him to the hospital for physical
examinations and the results were always the same: everything
about him is normal except for his weight.
</P>
<P>
Deng entered primary school at the age of six, and he was among
the top three among more than 20 classmates. But he had to quit
school because of his obesity.
</P>
<P>
"What I want most now is to go back to school as soon as
possible," the boy said when asked what he wanted most.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
