<HEADLINE> China Intensifies Supervision of Steel Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China will further crack down on
fake and shoddy iron and steel products and standardize the
domestic market, according to an official with the State
Administration of the Metallurgical Industry.
</P>
<P>
China, the world's leading iron and steel producer, has an
annual output of over 100 million tons of related products.
Nonetheless, the metallurgical industry's profits dropped from a
record 29.4 billion yuan to only two billion yuan in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The sector plans to reduce its 1999 output by 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Yang Xiaoning, director of the Metallurgical Economic
Development Research Center, said that efforts to control the
gross output of iron and steel are designed to reverse the
imbalance in supply and demand, and stimulate market prices.
</P>
<P>
However, the fact that supply will fall short of demand on some
local markets will also provide an opportunity for an increase in
fake and shoddy products. Zhao Xizi, deputy director of the
administration, noted that it is absolutely essential to crack
down on such products. 
</P>
