<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Experiences Unseasonable Weather </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, the Chinese capital has
witnessed unseasonable weather featuring heavy fog, low visibility,
high humidity, occasional periods of sporadic sleet and lower
temperatures over the past 10 days.
</P>
<P>
The Capital International Airport was forced to close during
various periods owing to heavy fog which also led to an increase
in motor vehicle accidents in urban districts.
</P>
<P>
Experts with the Beijing Meteorological Observatory explained
that the unseasonable weather has been caused by the arrival of
weak cold fronts from north.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the fact that central heating is still available
in most of the capital's residential areas has increased the
volume of coal dust and smoke emissions in the thick cloud cover.
The failure of low pressure and weak breezes has in turn resulted
in increased pollution levels in the city.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists note that the unseasonable weather will linger
for at least one or two more days. Strong winds expected around
March 20 will ease the pollution problem somewhat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
