<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Agriculture
of Ethiopia has said encouraging results have been achieved in the
 afforestation drive in the country in the last five years.
</P>
<P>
According to "the Ethiopian Herald" Wednesday, Tamiru Habte, an
official from the ministry told local press that the government's
new policy envisages the development of forest over 8,000 hectares
of land annually.
</P>
