<HEADLINE> Abu Dhabi Most Expensive City in Gulf: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates'
capital Abu Dhabi is the most expensive city in the Gulf region
for foreigners, the Gulf News said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Abu Dhabi ranks 26th, with a score of 94, in the list of 100
most expensive cities in the world, the daily said, quoting the
results of a Swiss survey of living costs in world cities.
</P>
<P>
The world's most expensive cities are Tokyo with a score of
165, Hong Kong, 153 and Beijing, 152, the survey said.
</P>
<P>
The annual survey was made by the Corporate Resources Group of
the consultant William M Mercer Companies.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey, another UAE city, Dubai, also figures
in the top 50, ranked 49th with a score of 87.
</P>
<P>
Other Gulf cities listed are Riyadh, ranked 32nd with a score
of 92; Kuwait, ranked 33rd with a score of 91; Jeddah, ranked 41
with a score of 88; and Manama, ranked 46 with a score of 87.
</P>
<P>
The cost of living index was based on a survey carried out last
autumn. 
</P>
