<HEADLINE> Tourism Education System Takes Shape in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Tourism-related education is
improving and playing an important role in promoting China's fast-
growing travel industry.
</P>
<P>
By 1997, according to today's Overseas Edition of the People's
Daily, China had set up 192 tourism-related schools of higher
learning and 744 secondary vocational schools.
</P>
<P>
More than 50,000 tourist guides have passed examinations and
been licensed since the practice was introduced in 1989.
</P>
<P>
Over 13,770 travel agency managers have passed examinations and
received licenses since the scheme was started in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Last year similar examinations for tourist group leaders were
introduced.
</P>
<P>
China's tourism education sector has so far established ties
and conducted exchanges with their counterparts in over 20
countries and regions and the World Tourism Organization and the
Pacific Asia Tourism Association.  
</P>
</TEXT>
