<HEADLINE> CPC Central Committee Calls For Education Of Officials (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) has suggested educating Party and
government officials in the Party spirit and work style,
explaining that such a drive will improve their general qualities.
</P>
<P>
Focusing on study, political awareness and healthy ethics, the
drive will start among leading officials at and above the county
level across the country in two years, according to a notice of
the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Although China has enjoyed considerable achievements in
education drives of this kind in past years, there are still
unresolved problems.
</P>
<P>
It notes that changing situations and tasks bring both
opportunities and challenges but at the same time place new and
higher demands on officials, which concern their ability to solve
complicated problems in a practical way.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the emphasis on study, political awareness and
healthy ethics will be crucial in improving the genral qualities
of officials, and ensuring the overall implementation of the
Party's basic theory, guideline and principles, as well as helping
with the smooth progress of the reform, opening-up and
modernization drive, the document notes.
</P>
<P>
It acknowledges that leading officials in the Party are in
general more than adequate in their duties, but a number of them
still cannot cope with the demands of changing situations in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990317.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Central Committee Calls For Education Of Officials (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The document puts forward basic requirements for educating
officials, saying that they should hold firm the belief of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics and keep in line
with the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
The officials should demonstrate and implement organizational
skills, leadership and working practices featuring democracy under
centralized guidance.
</P>
<P>
They should earnestly practice the principle of serving the
people wholeheartedly and get rid of bureaucracy and other corrupt
behavior that hurts the state and the people's interest.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the officials must vigorously promote the search for
truth, making sure their words are reflected in their actions, the
document says, adding that personal vanity and fraud must be
banned in the Party.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the education principles, the document stresses
personal improvement, following the Party's basic line, promoting
democracy inside the Party while maintaining criticism and self-
criticism, and says that such education must be conducted under
the Deng Xiaoping Theory and the guideline of the 15th CPC
National Congress.  
</P>
</TEXT>
