<HEADLINE> BOC Provides Consumer Credit to Car Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) will to
provide consumer credit to car purchasers and dealers for the
Dongfeng-Citroen Automobile Corp. this year, according to an
agreement between the bank and the Chinese auto manufacturer.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement which was signed on Monday, the BOC will
help the Sino-French joint venture sell its Fukang model cars
using the credit plan.
</P>
<P>
However, the two sides did not specify the exact amount of
money involved in the loan package.
</P>
<P>
"How many loans will be extended depends on the actual market
demand for Fukang cars," said an industry insider.
</P>
<P>
The BOC has granted 1.5 billion U.S. dollars to Dongfeng-
Citroen since May 1992, and last year the car maker sold about 36,
000 cars, up 20 percent from 1997, with sales volume hitting 3.5
billion yuan (421 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Dongfeng-Citroen has set its output target this year at 55,000
units. "Car sales are expected to increase this year because of a
package of government measures intended to stimulate domestic
consumption and the purchase of houses, cars, and electric
appliances," said Zhang Shiduan, president of the company.
</P>
<P>
With an investment of 10.3 billion yuan as an economic backup,
the Wuhan-based joint venture's plant intends to produce 150,000
cars annually when in full operation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
