<HEADLINE> Chopper Crash Kills 19 in Far Eastern Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, March 17 (Xinhua) -- A Mi-8 helicopter crashed late
Tuesday on the Kamchatka Peninsula in Far Eastern Russia, killing
19 of the 26 people on board, Itar-Tass reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seven survivors have been hospitalized and four of them
are listed as in serious condition.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter, of the regional Krechet Airlines, was flying
from the Sobolevo township on the peninsula's western coast to
Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky. An investigation has been launched to
establish the cause of the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
This was the second Mi-8 crash this week. The last one
happened on Sunday when a U.N.-chartered helicopter went down in
Haiti. All 13 people aboard, including six Russians, six
Argentines and one American, were killed. 
</P>
