<HEADLINE> Qinghai Collects Historical Data on Minority Ethnic Groups </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The goal of the campaign is to compile valuable reference
material for future studies of the province's five largest
minority ethnic groups. Dozens of researchers have been sent to
remote monasteries and rural areas in Gansu and Qinghai provinces
to collect ancient books, folk legends and other rare historical
data.
</P>
<P>
La Bingde, an official with the Qinghai Provincial Religious
Affairs Commission, said the material will be translated and a
comprehensive book covering the politics, economies, cultures,
education levels, religions and customs of the ethnic groups will
be published before the year 2000.
