<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 17 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government is to
provide scholarships to 1,000 high school students who have
talents for sports but whose parents cannot afford their schooling.
</P>
<P>
"The program is expected to materialize soon and it is
important to continue it in the future," Youth and Sports Minister
Agung Laksono said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has prepared the mechanisms for scholarships so
recipient students can improve their academic as well as sport
performance, Laksono said.
</P>
<P>
