sporting talents from students throughout the country, especially
for high school students.
</P>
<P>
To date, Laksono said, sports performance amongst students
needs financial support and continued training.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there is a need for more sport teachers, sports
equipment and special sport schools for talented students.
</P>
<P>
Islamic schools should also provide the chance to their
students to improve sporting achievements without abandoning their
study on religious affairs, Laksono was quoted by the Indonesian
Observer Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Another problem for students is that sports education is often
stopped after they finish high school and enter college.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, universities should also provide sport facilities
so that new athletes could emerge from campuses," Laksono added.
</P>
