<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai To Develop New Economic Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Chongming Island, China's third
largest island at the mouth of the Yangtze River, is expected to
become another major development area in the coming century,
following the Pudong New Area, an emerging financial and trade
zone in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the municipal government said Shanghai, the nation's
leading industrial and commercial center, is now making plans to
turn the 1,000-sq-km island into a center for new industries.
</P>
<P>
Priority is to be put on the development of free trade,
transfer shipping, export-oriented processing, eco-agriculture and
island tourism, the sources noted.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for massive construction, the municipality will soon
launch a series of infrastructure projects, including a tunnel
connecting the island with the city proper.
</P>
<P>
The idea is part of an overall blueprint for Shanghai to become
an international economic center by the year 2010. According to
the plan, a number of satellite towns will be built around the
city.
</P>
<P>
Chongming, which boasts 20,000 hectares of beaches and shoals
and abounds with natural resources, is approximately twice the
size of the Pudong New Area and has historically had an
agricultural focus.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990317.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast China Airport Reopens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the sources,the airport closed at 7 a.m. yesterday.
The snowfall lasted for more than eight hours, and snow at the
airport was five cm deep, with visibility estimated at about 400
meters. The runway was full of snow and the ground was quite
slippery.
</P>
<P>
During the closure, at least 30 inbound and outbound flights
were canceled. But all the stranded passengers were properly
accommodated.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this month, Shenyang has been hit by
abrupt climatic changes, including several snowfalls which have
affected normal airport operations.
</P>
<P>
On March 4, the airport closed for 13 hours due to a heavy
storm which dumped 13 centimeters of snow on the northeastern city.
</P>
