<HEADLINE> College Students Moved by Ancient Chinese Poetry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- College students outside Beijing
are to be given the chance to appreciate ancient Chinese poetry
thanks to a series of special readings featuring famous works from
the Tang (618-907) and Song (960-1279) dynasties.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Beijing Concert Hall, the recital, which began
on Monday this week and last to the end of March, will tour
universities in Tianjin, Nanjing, Shanghai, Xiamen, and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
Last month, a recital of Chinese ancient poetry was performed
at the Beijing Concert Hall.
</P>
<P>
Recited were a dozen Chinese ancient poems that were composed
by well-known poets in Tang and Song dynasties, with music
background.
</P>
<P>
A student from Tianjin's Nankai University said that he is
overcome with the eternal charm of such poetry which helps improve
the nation's cultural appreciation and boosts Chinese self-esteem
and pride.
</P>
<P>
The manager of Beijing Concert Hall said that any income from
the performances will be donated to the "China Hope Project", the
acclaimed educational scheme, to help establish two music primary
schools in Chongqing Municipality and Henan Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
