<HEADLINE> China Launches Publicity Drive to Popularize Coal Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- China is launching a massive
publicity campaign to popularize laws and regulations concerning
the coal industry among its vast coal enterprises and workers
nationwide, in a bid to ensure a sound development of the sector.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official with the State Administration of
Coal Industry, the current coal law publicity drive focuses on
explicit stipulations to guide and ensure the exploration of coal
resources, safe production, the issuing of coal production permits,
special protection for coal miners as well as the transportation
and marketing of coal.
</P>
<P>
He said that popularization of laws including the Coal Law
among coal enterprises and workers is an important means to ensure
sound development of the coal industry, adding that China produces
nearly 1.3 billion tons of raw coal annually and is the world's
largest coal producer and consumer. The coal sector accounts for
75 percent of the country's energy resources production and
consumption.
</P>
<P>
However, in some parts of the country, there still exists
rampant illegal mining of coal resources, an overall waste in the
industry, accidents which lead to injuries and death, damage to
coal mines, and the irregular transportation and management of
coal products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
