<HEADLINE> Brazil Stock Markets Register Sustained Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The stock markets of Sao
Paulo and Rio de Janiero closed on Tuesday with sustained growth
for the second consecutive day, owing to news of renewed help for
Brazilian exporters.
</P>
<P>
Sao Paulo closed with a rise of 2.35 percent, after gaining 8.
77 percent the previous day, while Rio de Janiero rose three
percent, after a gain of 4.3 percent on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The operators in Sao Paulo said encouraging news from the
annual meeting of the Inter-American Development Bank (IDB) had a
positive effect on the exchange market, where the real continues
to gain against the U.S. dollar, which closed on Tuesday at 1.88
reals, compared to 2.25 reals in mid-February.
</P>
<P>
One of the achievements of the IDB meeting has been the
reactivating of external loans for Brazilian exporters, who this
year have 28 billion U.S. dollars in exterior credits. 
</P>
