<HEADLINE> Croats Condemn Attempted Assassination of Bosnian Croat Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZEGREB, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Croats in Croatia and Bosnia on
Tuesday condemned an attempted assassination of a Bosnian Croat
leader in Sarajevo.
</P>
<P>
Latest news reports said that Bosnian Croat Deputy Interior
Minister Jozo Leutar was seriously wounded in a car bomb explosion
early on Tuesday. He has been rushed to hospital for a surgery.
</P>
<P>
Another two people were also injured by the explosion, which
was put in the front of Leutar's car.
</P>
<P>
In statements, Croatian Foreign Ministry and its embassy in
Bosnia strongly condemned "the accident as a terrorist killing of
Croatian high-ranking officials" and called it "part of an attack
and murder campaign against Bosnian Croatians."
</P>
<P>
The attacks of this nature have "delayed the peace process in
Bosnia," the statements added.
</P>
<P>
Ante Jelavic, Croat member of Bosnia's joint presidency, said
in a statement on Tuesday that the attack amounted to "an
explosive device against all Croats in Bosnia-Hercegovina."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the international representatives in Bosnia also
expressed their condemnation against the terrorist act. 
</P>
