<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Zoo keepers in Jinan Zoo, in the
capital city of east China's Shandong Province, are considering
artificial breeding methods for a range of rare animals in their
care who have not mated because of the unnatural conditions or the
lack of a compatible mate.
</P>
<P>
The zoo has around 200 different animals with nearly 40 of them
listed as state-level rare species.
</P>
<P>
But a fifth of them have failed to mate including two snow
leopards who arrived in 1984 and a 26-year-old chimpanzee named "
Lao Wen". The zoo also owns a 23-year-old African female elephant
but her mate cannot be found easily as the male is often difficult
to keep in captivity. 
