<HEADLINE> China's Shanxi Attracts More Foreign Funds for Its Highway Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Northern China's Shanxi Province
has used 2.88 billion yuan (347 million U.S. dollars) of foreign
investment for highway construction in the last three years.
</P>
<P>
The provincial transportation administration has made great
efforts to improve the investment environment in the area of
transportation construction since 1996, and its work efficiency
has attracted many foreign investment companies to expand their
business in the province.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, 22 highway-construction joint ventures have been
set up in the province, and investment from the United States,
South Korea, Australia, and Hong Kong has reached 2.88 billion
yuan over the past three years, with 1.53 billion yuan of
investment last year alone.  
</P>
