<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Calls for Commitments to Peace in Southeastern Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan
Kostov told Parliament Tuesday that Bulgaria expects the
Rambouillet peace deal to restore security and stability in the
region and lead to a strong commitment on the part of the entire
international community to the future of Southeastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
At the request of MPs, Kostov set forth Bulgaria's position on
a solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
"We expect not only the hostilities to cease, but also a
lasting solution to be found, based on the provisional agreement
backed by the Contact Group and the European Union; a solution
which will stand the test of everyday contacts between the
citizens in Kosovo and in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia
regardless of their ethnic origin," the Bulgarian Prime Minister
said.
</P>
<P>
The solution to Kosovo must establish a model of interethnic
relations that would put Yugoslavia back on the map of Europe and
thanks to which the social processes in the neighboring countries
would no longer be held hostage to the existing climate in the
region.
</P>
<P>
"The Bulgarian Government is hopeful about the talks on Kosovo
in France," Kostov said.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Bulgaria's support for the presence of
international peacekeeping forces in Kosovo, if the two parties to
the conflict accept the Rambouillet agreement.
</P>
<P>
Kostov confirmed that Bulgaria favors a political solution of
the Kosovo conflict.
</P>
<P>
Any military solution resulting from a refusal to accept the
agreement in France will lead to disintegration of the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
He categorically condemned the violence in Kosovo and argued in
favor of an unconditional restoration of the human rights of
Kosovo Albanians.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he said that the demands for the independence
of Kosovo were unacceptable to Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
"Bulgaria supports the achievement of a peaceful solution by
political means which should guarantee the fundamental rights and
freedoms of all Kosovo residents regardless of their ethnic origin
on the basis of granting a broad autonomy to Kosovo within the
internationally recognized borders of the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia and respect for its territorial integrity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
