<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Marseille, Atletico, Parma and Bologna Reach UEFA Semis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Atletico Madrid spoiled the
Italian hopes of having a record three teams in the UEFA Cup semi-
finals with a rallied 2-1 away victory over nine-man Roma on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Atletico booked their place in the last four 4-2 on aggregate
after Parma handed out a 6-0 drubbing to French league leaders
Girondins for a 7-2 aggregate win. Bologna slipped through 3-2
overall after a 2-0 second leg defeat by Olympique Lyon.
</P>
<P>
Olympique Marseille ended Celta Vigo's giant-killing run by
drawing 0-0 in the second leg in Spain and qualifying 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Roma had Cameroon defender Pierre Woma sent off in the 28th
minute but went 1-0 ahead through striker Marco Delvecchio four
minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Atletico fought back to draw level through Carlos Aguilera in
the 59th minute before Roberto Fresnedoso sent the Spanish side
through with an 89th minute goal.
</P>
<P>
Roma's misery was complete when skipper Francesco Totti was
sent off for a second caution in the 90th minute.
</P>
<P>
Olympique Marseille dashed the hopes of another Spanish team as
they went through thanks to a 2-1 first leg win after forcing out
a goaless tie with Celta Vigo, who had beaten England's Aston
Villa and Liverpool in previous rounds.
</P>
<P>
Parma, who lost their first leg match 1-2 two weeks ago,
completely turned around the table by crushing Bordeaux 6-0 thanks
to their lethal striking partnership Hernan Crespo and Enrico
Chiesa.
</P>
<P>
Argentine Crespo began the demolition of the Girondins in the
37th minute and Italian Chiesa struck in the 43rd for a 2-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
Midfielder Juan Veron joined compatriot Crespo on the
scoresheet in the 48th minute before Crespo and Chiesa contributed
their second apiece in the 59th and 66th minutes.
</P>
<P>
Argentine Abel Balbo converted a penalty to complete the 6-0
rout.
</P>
<P>
Another Italian side Bologna turned in a lacklustre performance
at Olympique Lyon, losing 0-2, but they still went through 3-2 on
aggregate.
</P>
<P>
The draw for the semifinals will be made in Zurich on March 19,
with the ties taking place on April 6 and 20. The final will be
in Moscow on May 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
