<HEADLINE> New Bridge for Southwest Chinese County </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, March 17 (Xinhua) -- Qijiang County of Chongqing
Municipality in southwest China will build another bridge at a
point about 40 meters from the site of the collapsed Hongqiao
bridge on the Qihe River.
</P>
<P>
The Hongqiao bridge collapsed on January 4 this year, claiming
40 lives.
</P>
<P>
The new bridge, also named the Hongqiao, will be built at a
cost of ten million yuan, mainly provided by local government,
according to Xu Tingjiang, deputy magistrate of the county.
</P>
<P>
A public bid for the bridge's design will be held on March 20.
Construction of the bridge, connecting a commercial downtown area
and a residential area, is expected to begin in mid-May and be
completed in one year, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
The local government has vowed to give priority to quality in
the course of completing this project. A plaque will be placed
near the new Hongqiao bridge in memory of those who died last
January. 
</P>
