conference on women and sport closed here on Tuesday after
endorsing a draft resolution calling for more women's involvement
in sports.
</P>
<P>
The Women and Sport Conference 1999, themed "Women and Sport:
New Horizons", is aimed at "increasing the participation of women
and girls in sports in Singapore at all levels and in all
functions and roles", according to the resolution.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day session, sports officials, staff of local
schools, visiting foreign scholars and students discussed
solutions to the barriers which keep women away from sports in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Only 28 percent of the country's women participated regularly
in sports in 1997, compared to 40 percent of males, according to a
recent survey.
</P>
<P>
The resolution called for women's equity in sport, more
accessibility of facilities for women and more sporting education
available. 
