<HEADLINE> Dow Crosses 10,000 Mark But Turns Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
NEW YORK, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial
average crossed 10,000 mark for the first time Tuesday but
turned back mainly because of profit taking.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip stock index climbed to 10,001.78 within 21
minutes after opening of the session. Then the index slipped
back and ended its historic day with a modest loss.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed at 9,930.47, down 28.30. The index gained
82.42 points at 9,958.77 Monday in march forward to the 10,000
milestone.
</P>
<P>
Favorable earnings for a number of companies helped the
index to top the 10,000 mark. Investors rushed into the market
as Union Carbide reported a strong earnings forecast and
Merck secured FDA approval for a new use of its Mevacor drug
but they began profit takings after the composite broke the
10,000 mark.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nasdaq index fell 7.83 at 2,439.27. The
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 0.90 at 1,306.36.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 1.14 at 614.08 and the American Stock
Exchange composite index fell 4.60 at 716.31. The Russell 2000
index of smaller companies was down 1.67 at 399.17.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 9-to-7 margin on
New York Stock Exchange, with 1,688 down, 1,313 up and 568
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased to 738.88 million shares from 724.55
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
